      "section": "A",
      "maximumMark": 6,
      "topic": "functions",
      "skill_tag": "quadratic_functions",
      "parts": [
        {
          "label": "a",
          "body": "Find $f(2)$.",
          "marks": 2,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "substitute $x = 2$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$f(2) = -5$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$f(2) = -5$",
          "solution": "$$f(2) = 3(2)^2 - 12(2) + 7 = 12 - 24 + 7 = -5$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(3*2**2 - 12*2 + 7, -5)"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Find the two values of $x$ for which $f(x) = 0$, giving your answers to three significant figures.",
          "marks": 4,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "solve $3x^2 - 12x + 7 = 0$ (GDC or quadratic formula)"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "discriminant $144 - 84 = 60$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x \\approx 0.709$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$x \\approx 3.29$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$x \\approx 0.709$ or $x \\approx 3.29$",
          "solution": "**Plan:** solve the quadratic with the GDC (or formula).$$x = \\frac{12 \\pm \\sqrt{144 - 84}}{6} = \\frac{12 \\pm \\sqrt{60}}{6} = 2 \\pm \\frac{\\sqrt{15}}{3}$$$$x \\approx 0.709 \\text{ or } x \\approx 3.29$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(2 - sqrt(15)/3 - 0.709) < 0.00051",
            "Abs(2 + sqrt(15)/3 - 3.29) < 0.0051"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "The function $f$ is given by $f(x) = 3x^2 - 12x + 7$."
    },
    {
