          ],
          "answer": "$0.267$ (3 sf)",
          "solution": "**Plan:** binomial probability with $n = 10$, $p = 0.3$.$$P(X = 3) = \\binom{10}{3}(0.3)^3(0.7)^7 = 0.2668\\ldots \\approx 0.267$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(binomial(10, 3)*Rational(3, 10)**3*Rational(7, 10)**7 - 0.267) < 0.00051"
          ]
        },
        {
          "label": "b",
          "body": "Find $P(X \\ge 1)$, giving your answer to three significant figures.",
          "marks": 3,
          "markscheme": [
            {
              "mark": "M1",
              "note": "use the complement $P(X \\ge 1) = 1 - P(X = 0)$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$P(X = 0) = (0.7)^{10}$"
            },
            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "$P(X \\ge 1) \\approx 0.972$"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$0.972$ (3 sf)",
          "solution": "The complement of \"at least one\" is \"none\":$$P(X \\ge 1) = 1 - (0.7)^{10} = 0.9718\\ldots \\approx 0.972$$",
          "verify": [
            "Abs(1 - Rational(7, 10)**10 - 0.972) < 0.00051"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "A biased coin lands heads with probability $0.3$. It is tossed 10 times. Let $X$ be the number of heads, so $X \\sim B(10,\\ 0.3)$."
    },
