            {
              "mark": "A1",
              "note": "displacement $= 4$ m"
            }
          ],
          "answer": "$4$ m",
          "solution": "Displacement is the integral of velocity:$$\\int_0^4 (3t^2 - 12t + 9)\\,dt = \\left[t^3 - 6t^2 + 9t\\right]_0^4$$$$= (64 - 96 + 36) - 0 = 4 \\text{ m}$$",
          "verify": [
            "Eq(integrate(3*t**2 - 12*t + 9, (t, 0, 4)), 4)"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "contextIntro": "A particle moves in a straight line. Its velocity, in metres per second, at time $t$ seconds is $v(t) = 3t^2 - 12t + 9$ for $t \\ge 0$."
    },
